Hello so, this is my first SCP, though I've been around for years so I get what goes into a good SCP probably. This one has undergone several drafts and revisions, both private and otherwise. Posted once, it died, so I've spent a few months reworking it a bit to focus on what worked and scrap some relics of old habits.

The idea here was to tell a story: SCP-4678 on its own is basically a monster manual object on purpose. I wanted it to be simple, because its not the focus of the article, its the tool that enables the real story- the story of a researcher who can't move on from a recent trauma, or even acknowledge it properly to begin to come to terms with it, and pushes himself too hard because of it. And the consequences of this.

I figure the most contentious part will be SCP-073's inclusion, but given the themes of regret and moving on from the past etc, and the origins of Cain and Able in biblical text, and that he gave me a route to work in a cool apocalypse scenario for the climax, he was overall just a perfect fit for the story I wanted to tell.







