The testing log was mainly to show how efficient Charles has been, wasting no time coming up with a somewhat cruel but very effective way to test for certain how it works, and then being handwaved when Ethics is brought in by 05-7, who I pictured having an interest in this sort of thing, considering he is the one who replies immediately to the request at the bottom, and green lights the project in the first place himself.

As for the grammar stuff though I'll sort it out quickly. I tend to try to Type how I talk, it makes text easier to interpret tone in, but that bleeds over into non-casual writing as well hence all the commas.







